125179196.Body:
It's currently impossible to make an existing node a child of a package node. It should be enabled, e.g., by moving the node over the package node. Once this is possible, the behavior of the copy/cut-paste should be changed so that pasted node are not pasted into their parent (in the case of class diagram nodes).

We don't really have the concept of a Context Menu for elements at this point. This will have to be for the future. For this issue, we can keep the UI part simple. What about the following for the shift key to attach/detach children from parents?

### Tentative specs (if the shift key is pressed)
* If all selected nodes don't have a parent and can be added as children of the node under the mouse point, attach them to the parent, otherwise, do nothing.
* If all selected nodes have the same parent, detach them from the parent, otherwise, do nothing.

This functionality will require a new type of command, namely, attach/detach commands.

### To detect Shift Key Presses in DiagramTab

We could do this:

1. add this interface in the `.gui` package:

```java
public interface ShiftKeyPressedHandler
{
	void keyPressed();
}
```
2. Declare `DiagramTab` to implement this interface, providing as handler e.g.,:

```java
public void keyPressed()
{
   System.out.println("Shif key pressed in " + aDiagram.getDescription());
}
```

3. In the constructor of `EditorFrame`, add:

```java
setOnKeyPressed(e -> 
{
   if( e.isShiftDown() && !isWelcomeTabShowing() )
   {
      getSelectedDiagramTab().keyPressed();
   }
});
```

